<emphasis id="8DB6EAE1FFB41B03FC33FC2D02DE45F4" box="[1001,1496,920,962]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="160">
<taxonomicName id="78C24D70FFB41B03FC33FC2D02D445F4" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1853" box="[1001,1490,920,962]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Cryptolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montrouzieri">Cryptolaemus montrouzieri</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but there is no record of it. vVe found it occasionally in 1936. It feeds on soft scales.
</paragraph>
